      <TextArea accessibleRole="TEXT" editable="false" layoutX="112.0" layoutY="51.0" mouseTransparent="true" prefHeight="596.0" prefWidth="931.0" style="-fx-text-fill: black;" text="&#10;&#10;Hamka is based on the classic board.  &#10;The game includes some additional rules:&#10;1. A queen is able to move beyond the border of the board and relocate on its opposite side.&#10;2. If a player makes a valid move he's granted with points that are the difference ( positive or negative ) &#10;   between the passed seconds to 1 minute.&#10;3. A player is granted 100 points for eating checkers of the opponent.&#10;4. The game is finished when one of the player runs out of checkers, or if the current player can't move at all; &#10;   The winner is the player who has earned more points.&#10;&#10;Moreover, the game also includes special tiles.&#10;&#10;      &#10;       Yellow Tile- Every turn 3 tiles with no checkers are painted with Yellow. if the current player steps on one of them he will be asked a question.&#10;The questions are divided to 3 levels: easy, medium and hard. If the player gives the correct answer for easy question,&#10;he gets 100, medium-200, hard-500.&#10;For wrong answer he loses 250 points for easy question, medium-100, hard-50.&#10;&#10;       Green tile-If the player doesn't make a move after 30 seconds, one of the reachable tiles for him will be painted with green. &#10;If he steps on such tile, he will be granted 50 points.&#10;&#10;       Red tile- Every turn a red tile appears on one of the reachable tiles for the player. &#10;Stepping on such tile gives him another move in the same turn only if it's possible. &#10;In such case he will be marked with red on the sides. If the checker that stepps on a red tile is a queen it will be marked with purple.&#10;&#10;       Orange tile- If the player doesn't make a move after 90 seconds, all of the reachable tiles for him will be painted with orange.&#10;&#10;       Blue tile- If a player is left with 2 regular checkers and one queen, one of the free tiles will be painted with blue. &#10;Stepping on such tile opens a pop up screen with a mini checker board. &#10;The player is then able to restore one of his checkers that were excluded, to tiles that are far more than 2 free tiles from every opponent checker.&#10;&#10;Moreover, if a player is punished for not eating, we won't be given any of the priviliges given by stepping on special tiles, &#10;and one of his checkers that could eat will be excluded.">
